crates/ctx-context/tests/ is the integration-test surface for the chain-resolution and hook/session-dedup contracts that the rest of ctx-context depends on but that no single source file's unit tests exercise end-to-end. Nothing here is imported elsewhere; its value is pinning cross-module behavior (serve + hook + session) against a shared in-memory environment fake.

Both test files define their own `FakeEnv` (flat `BTreeMap<path, bytes>` over `ctx_context::env::Env`, with `is_dir` inferred from key prefixes) rather than sharing one — an editor changing directory-detection semantics in one file's fake must mirror the change in the other's or the two suites will silently diverge on edge cases like empty-segment paths. chain_serve.rs pins the traversal contract of `serve::chain_for`/`serve::render` (rollup+intent per level, descending root-to-leaf, then leaf ctx; path-escape rejection; soft-missing markers instead of errors). hook_session.rs pins the session-ledger contract: hook events and CLI path-mode dispatch share one session cache file (`.context/.cache/hook-<session_id>.json`), deduping already-shown ancestor context, fail-open on corrupt cache, and no-op when no session env is set.

A change to path-escape validation, chain ordering, or the absent-scaffolding sentinel strings must update chain_serve.rs; a change to session-cache location, keying, or fail-open behavior must update hook_session.rs — the two are independent contracts and rarely need joint edits. hook_session.rs's `FakeEnv::seeded()` fixture shape (root + crates/foo with rollup/intent/leaf ctx, sibling bar.rs/baz.rs) is load-bearing for its dedup assertions; new tests in that file should extend rather than replace it.

No intent.md exists for this directory.